meal_plan.meal_plan_text:
DAY 1 MEAL PLAN

Pre-workout (05:30 AM)
Meal: Quick Protein Apple
Ingredients:
- Apple, sliced: 1 medium (approx 180g)
- Peanut Butter: 15g
- Vegetarian Protein Powder: 15g
Preparation: Slice apple. Mix protein powder with a tablespoon of water into a thick paste and serve with apple slices and peanut butter.
Macros: 235 calories, 17g protein, 30g carbs, 9g fats

Post-workout Breakfast (07:30 AM)
Meal: High-Protein Berry Oatmeal
Ingredients:
- Rolled Oats (dry): 60g
- Unsweetened Almond Milk: 200ml
- Vegetarian Protein Powder: 30g
- Greek Yogurt (0% fat): 150g
- Mixed Berries: 100g
- Chia Seeds: 10g
Preparation: Cook oats with almond milk. Stir in protein powder, Greek yogurt, and chia seeds after cooking. Top with berries.
Macros: 525 calories, 50g protein, 63g carbs, 9g fats

Morning Snack (10:30 AM)
Meal: Cottage Cheese with Fruit and Seeds
Ingredients:
- Cottage Cheese (low fat): 200g
- Mixed Berries: 50g
- Chia Seeds: 10g
Preparation: Combine cottage cheese, berries, and chia seeds in a bowl.
Macros: 230 calories, 31g protein, 17g carbs, 7g fats

Lunch (1:00 PM)
Meal: High-Protein Lentil Pasta Bolognese
Ingredients:
- Red Lentil Pasta (dry): 50g
- Vegetarian Ground (soy-based or similar): 80g
- Passata (tomato sauce): 200g
- Onion, chopped: 50g
- Bell Pepper, chopped: 50g
- Olive Oil: 10g
- Nutritional Yeast: 15g
Preparation: Cook pasta according to package directions. While pasta cooks, heat oil in a pan, sauté onion and pepper until soft. Add vegetarian ground and cook until browned. Stir in passata and nutritional yeast, simmer for 5-10 minutes. Serve sauce over pasta.
Macros: 530 calories, 38g protein, 58g carbs, 17g fats

Afternoon Snack (4:00 PM)
Meal: High-Protein Shake
Ingredients:
- Vegetarian Protein Powder: 35g
- Unsweetened Almond Milk: 300ml
- Peanut Butter: 10g
Preparation: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Macros: 245 calories, 36g protein, 10g carbs, 8g fats

Dinner (7:00 PM)
Meal: High-Protein Loaded Sweet Potato
Ingredients:
- Sweet Potato: 150g
- Black Beans (canned, rinsed): 100g
- Corn (canned or frozen): 50g
- Tempeh: 150g
- Taco Seasoning: 5g
- Olive Oil: 3g
- Greek Yogurt (0% fat): 50g
- Shredded Cheddar Cheese (Reduced Fat): 20g
- Salsa: 30g
Preparation: Bake or microwave sweet potato until tender. Crumble tempeh and toss with taco seasoning and oil. Pan-fry tempeh until browned and slightly crispy. Heat black beans and corn. Split sweet potato, mash slightly, top with seasoned tempeh, black beans, corn, Greek yogurt, cheese, and salsa.
Macros: 695 calories, 50g protein, 78g carbs, 25g fats

DAY 2 MEAL PLAN

Pre-workout (05:30 AM)
Meal: Banana with Protein & Peanut Butter
Ingredients:
- Banana: 1 medium (approx 120g)
- Vegetarian Protein Powder: 20g
- Peanut Butter: 10g
Preparation: Mix protein powder with a tablespoon of water to form a thick paste. Slice banana and serve with peanut butter and the protein paste for dipping/spreading.
Macros: 240 calories, 20g protein, 31g carbs, 6g fats

Post-workout Breakfast (07:30 AM)
Meal: High-Protein Green Smoothie with Oats
Ingredients:
- Vegetarian Protein Powder: 40g
- Rolled Oats (dry): 20g
- Spinach: 50g
- Banana: 100g
- Unsweetened Almond Milk: 300ml
- Greek Yogurt (0% fat): 100g
- Chia Seeds: 10g
- Peanut Butter: 10g
Preparation: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Macros: 530 calories, 52g protein, 56g carbs, 13g fats

Morning Snack (10:30 AM)
Meal: Cottage Cheese with Fruit and Seeds
Ingredients:
- Cottage Cheese (low fat): 200g
- Mixed Berries: 50g
- Chia Seeds: 10g
Preparation: Combine cottage cheese, berries, and chia seeds in a bowl.
Macros: 230 calories, 31g protein, 17g carbs, 7g fats

Lunch (1:00 PM)
Meal: High-Protein Lentil Pasta Marinara
Ingredients:
- Red Lentil Pasta (dry): 50g
- Vegetarian Ground (soy-based or similar): 80g
- Passata (tomato sauce): 200g
- Onion, chopped: 50g
- Bell Pepper, chopped: 50g
- Olive Oil: 10g
- Nutritional Yeast: 15g
Preparation: Cook pasta according to package directions. While pasta cooks, heat oil in a pan, sauté onion and pepper until soft. Add vegetarian ground and cook until browned. Stir in passata and nutritional yeast, simmer for 5-10 minutes. Serve sauce over pasta.
Macros: 530 calories, 38g protein, 58g carbs, 17g fats

Afternoon Snack (4:00 PM)
Meal: High-Protein Shake
Ingredients:
- Vegetarian Protein Powder: 35g
- Unsweetened Almond Milk: 300ml
- Peanut Butter: 10g
Preparation: Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Macros: 245 calories, 36g protein, 10g carbs, 8g fats

Dinner (7:00 PM)
Meal: High-Protein Veggie & Seitan Stir-fry
Ingredients:
- Cooked Brown Rice: 200g
- Seitan: 150g
- Mixed Stir-fry Vegetables (broccoli, peppers, carrots, snap peas): 200g
- Low Sodium Soy Sauce: 15ml
- Maple Syrup: 10g
- Cornstarch: 5g
- Sesame Oil: 10g
- Roasted Peanuts or Cashews: 20g
Preparation: Prepare sauce by mixing soy sauce, maple syrup, and cornstarch with a little water. Heat sesame oil in a wok or large pan. Add seitan and cook until browned. Add vegetables and stir-fry until tender-crisp. Pour sauce over stir-fry and cook until thickened. Serve over brown rice, topped with nuts.
Macros: 775 calories, 52g protein, 83g carbs, 27g fats
